    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_4_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_4",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, a masterclass in lightweight engineering and thermal management. This specimen features the 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, maintaining factory-spec boost pressure and impeccable compression across both rotors. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise short-throw five-speed manual gearbox and a Torsen limited-slip differential, providing exceptional power delivery. The chassis remains corner-balanced with its original double-wishbone suspension architecture and forged aluminum control arms, ensuring the 50/50 weight distribution is fully realized. Zero modifications, original paint depth, and a pristine interior make this a rare survivor of the golden era of JDM performance.",
